The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 September is 3,221 (372.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 September, there were 123 new confirmed cases (14.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 September, there were 121 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 2% (2 extra cases).
